         <abstract>
            <p>
               This record is the general record for the <foreign xml:lang="gez">Maṣḥafa qandil</foreign>, in cases where its recension
               is not known.
             The <foreign xml:lang="gez">Maṣḥafa qandil</foreign> is the ritual for the Unction of the Sick in the Ethiopian Church. 
               Each of its seven sections consists of the following elements:
             the lighting of a wick, a supplication, an epistle, the Trisagion, the Prayer of the Gospel with incensing and a 
               <foreign xml:lang="gez">mǝsbāk</foreign>, a Gospel reading and a prayer.
               Two recensions, which  correspond to the same  <ref target="#t2arabic">Arabic Vorlage</ref>, 
               but are different translations have been identified by
               <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Zanetti2010Qandil"/>
               </bibl> on the basis of printed editions.
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3952MashafaQ"/> corresponds to   <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Chaine1913Qandil"/> 
               </bibl> and the church editions, e.g.
               <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Tasfa1993Mashafa"/> 
               </bibl> and
               <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:TasfaQandil"/> 
               </bibl>.
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3953MashafaQ"/> corresponds to the edition     <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:1967Qandil"/> 
               </bibl>.
            </p>
         </abstract>
